		<div id="post_message_1379251">Look, that analysis of the article sucked balls.  What happened according to the article is, the passengers heard a scream and turned to find the assailant standing over the victim stabbing him.  The bus driver stopped the bus and everybody scrambled off the bus, including the driver, leaving the boy who'd already been stabbed a few times as a sacrifice while they saved their miserable hides.  Then, AFTER a truck driver stopped and ran over to see what the problem was, the Driver, the Trucker, and Caton re-entered the bus, and they saw the guy standing over the prone body of the boy, having gutted it, now in the process of decapitating it.  He got up and they ran away and he chased them to the door and they shut the door on his arm so he took one swipe and then pulled his arm back inside and went back to carving on the kid's body.  After the police showed up, they left the guy whittling away on the boy's body and waving his severed head around at them through the windows of the bus for hours, finally capturing him as he attempted to escape the bus.<br />
 <br />
At no time was that boy ever in any danger of being helped by a fellow human being, even when it might have saved his life.  I see more and more of this revolting cowardice in alleged adults, and I guess it's just another sign of the ongoing infantilization of the peoples of Western civilization.  Run and find an adult!</div>
