	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1379322" style="border-right: 1px solid #D1D1E1">
	
		
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Re: Cowards</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#D1D1E1; background-color:#D1D1E1" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		

		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1379322">It is easy to debate principles when you aren't face to face with the reality of the situation.<br />
<br />
The fact is, a stabbing is more likely to be fatal then a gunshot wound, and most people aren't willing to risk their lives (or those of their loved ones) for the sake of defending a corpse.  It isn't cowardice, it is common sense.  They armed themselves and contained the threat.  It sounds like they made the right decision to me, because nobody <i>else</i> was killed and the killer was taken into custody.<br />
<br />
If you want to take on someone wielding a hunting knife unarmed when you know they have no reservations in using it, by all means go for it.  It is ignorant to claim that the reason <i>those</i> people chose not to was due to cowardice.  Having no formal martial arts training, or being unwilling to put yourself at a lethal disadvantage against a murderer isn't cowardice, it is simply survival.<br />
<br />
Having said that, given the opportunity to respond to the situation in a manner that would subdue the attacker, I'd choose to subdue the attacker instead of simply fleeing the scene.  It sounds like everyone was completely caught by surprise, however, so protecting those unable to protect themselves was the priority.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		

		

		

	</td>
</tr>
